{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"zotero":1,"inscriptions":7,"isBulletin":212},{"title":2,"author":3,"date":4,"citation":5,"uri":6},"Olumpis Olumpios ed IG, XIV, 434","Gentile","2002","\u003Cspan>L. Gentile, «Olumpis Olumpios ed IG, XIV, 434», \u003Ci>Epigraphica\u003C/i> 64 (2002): 224–29\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/CJ9QP78X",[8],{"file":9,"uri":9,"title":10,"status":11,"editionAuthor":13,"type":14,"objectType":18,"material":22,"condition":28,"layoutDesc":29,"handNote":36,"date":128,"places":133,"geo":143,"country":138,"provenance":135,"provenanceGeo":147,"region":150,"settlement":140,"repository":151,"idno":155,"textLang":158,"tmNumber":162,"facsimile":163,"letterHeights":170,"publications":174,"zotero":184,"keywords":194,"html":204,"bibl":205,"bulletinDateSort":210,"citedRangeSort":211,"languageSort":159,"materialSort":23,"typeSort":15},"ISic001259","Statue base in honour of Olympis Mestos",{"_":12},"draft",null,{"_":15,"ana":16,"ref":17},"honorific","#function.honorific","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/69.html",{"_":19,"ana":20,"ref":21},"base","#object.base","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/57.html",{"_":23,"type":24,"resp":25,"ref":26,"subtype":27},"breccia","stone.breccia","#Coccato","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/73.html",[],"",{"layout":30},{"p":31,"rs":32,"damage":28},"The inscription is set out over four lines on the front face of the block on its upper half. The text is roughly centred, lines 1-3 filling the face, line 4 a single word approximately centered. Spacing between words is apparent and increases significantly in line 3.",{"_":33,"ana":34,"ref":35},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"lettering":37,"dimensions":114},[38,39],"The letters are regular and with terminal points rather than serfis, and are inscribed in parts in what is almost a punch style, rather than a chiselled groove. Alpha has broken bar; epsilon has mostly equal legnth cross-bars; theta has a full-width cross bar; kappa has full length bars; mu has vertical first and last, three-quarter length mid-strokes; omicron is full-size; pi has eual length verticals; rho has fair-sized closed eye; sigma has horizontal top and bottom strokes; omega is rhomboid and closed.",{"_":40,"ref":41},"\n                                    Types list:\n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                ",[42,45,48,51,54,57,60,63,66,69,72,75,78,81,84,87,90,93,96,99,102,105,108,111],{"_":43,"target":44},"Α type2","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type2.html",{"_":46,"target":47},"Ε type2","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.html",{"_":49,"target":50},"Ε type2.3","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.html",{"_":52,"target":53},"Ε type2.3.1","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.1.html",{"_":55,"target":56},"Ε type2.3.2","https://ki